				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Personally I hope that players will not be able to create click-links on the fly.  Right now the creation of clicklinks is limited.  If it becomes easily doable I think we'll start seeing people use it for griefing.  Meaning
<br />

<br />
&lt;a href = "charref://50000/1111111/&amp;quot;Test&amp;quot;"/quit"&gt;&amp;quot;Click here for something funny!&amp;quot;&lt;/a&gt;
<br />

<br />
Click the link and you just might get dropped off-line.  Actually probably cannot for a charref, but if you can create a clicklink with script, macro, or manual entry someone will use it to grief people.
<br />

<br />
If you can enter an itemref manually (or Script, or Macro) into chat you'll have people attempt to scam others with fake refs.  Again, you can accomplish it more easily, because the information isn't hard to figure out.  Being easier just brings the idiots out to play.<br />_________________<br /></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Beaker wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">usually it's caused by #2</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
