				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">about people having a bot using the old method:
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">$aoc-&gt;send_tell&#40; $nickname, $reply, $blob&#41;;</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
i suggest you do a new generic function like:
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">sendmsg&#40; $channel, $name, $reply, $blob&#41; &#123; ... &#125;
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">it's a minimum now.
<br />

<br />
Then you do a replace with notepad or whatever you use to edit your php files and you perform a systematic replacement of every occurence of <span style="font-weight: bold">$aoc-&gt;send_tell( </span>by <span style="font-weight: bold">sendmsg( "tell", </span>
<br />

<br />
When the new packet format will hit our servers, or even before on test and for good, we'll work inside the sendmsg function to adapt the output.
<br />
Personally i cant imagine to rewrite the whole bot. I will use the above method and ppl having this kind of function yet will do the same i think.
<br />

<br />
I have something seemingly to that:
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">function aosend&#40; $type, $to, $reply, $blob&#41;
<br />
&#123;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;global $aoc;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;global $bot_copy_channel;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;global $bot_copy_CG;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;global $myname;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;global $guild_name;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;global $bot_onCG;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;global $time_of_last_tell;
<br />

<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;switch&#40;$type&#41;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&#123;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;case&nbsp; 0 &#58;&nbsp; &nbsp;$aoc-&gt;send_tell&#40; $to, $reply, $blob&#41;;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;break;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;case&nbsp; 1 &#58;&nbsp; &nbsp;$aoc-&gt;send_privgroup&#40; $aoc-&gt;id&#91;$myname&#93;, $reply, $blob&#41;;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;if &#40;$bot_copy_channel==1 &amp;&amp; $bot_onCG==1&#41; $aoc-&gt;send_group&#40; &quot;$guild_name&quot;, $reply, $blob&#41;;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;break;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;case&nbsp; 2 &#58;&nbsp; &nbsp;if &#40;$bot_onCG==1&#41; $aoc-&gt;send_group&#40; &quot;$guild_name&quot;, $reply, $blob&#41;;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;if &#40;$bot_copy_CG==1&#41; $aoc-&gt;send_privgroup&#40; $aoc-&gt;id&#91;$myname&#93;, $reply, $blob&#41;;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;//echo &quot;&#91;TO_GC&#93;&#91;$guild_name&#93;&#58; $reply &quot;.$aoc-&gt;id&#91;$guild_name&#93;.&quot;\r\n&quot;;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;break;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;default &#58;&nbsp; &nbsp;break;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&#125;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;$time_of_last_tell = getmicrotime&#40;&#41;;
<br />
&#125;</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
or using beaker_queue_technology, you may add tells in the queue from this function, just after the new html blob conversion.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
